                                    compared to the Target Exposure Index as defined in IEC 62494-1;
                                    see PS 3.3 definition of Exposure Index Macro.

Factor (divisor or multiplicand) for normalizing a measurement;
                                    e.g., body surface area used for normalizing hemodynamic
                                    measurements

